	(51,7,'Jonathan','jonathan@thetapmusic.com','http://www.TheTapMusic.com','74.108.161.134','2010-12-01 18:28:38','2010-12-01 18:28:38','Hey Goodbye Picasso,\r\n \r\nI work for a newly launched music website promoting up-and-coming artists called The Tap Music.  Our site helps promote the placement of music into TV and commercials.  Some of our staff worked for a company that placed music in campaigns for Target, Mitsubishi, Levis, the Vancouver Olympics, Clinique, E-Trade, and more.  You may have spoken with our reps during the South By Southwest Festival or CMJ this year, too.\r\n  \r\nWeâ€™re reaching out to you because we came across your music and really liked your sound.  We would like to invite you to be on our new online music community â€“ TheTapMusic.com.  \r\n  \r\nEarlier this year, our team began building this online community to help emerging/lesser-known music acts establish themselves and connect with other bands, fans, as well as companies for licensing opportunities.   In fact, just 2 weeks ago we successfully placed the indie UK band â€œFezâ€ in an online Victoriaâ€™s Secret campaign that you can check out here: http://www.facebook.com/video/video.php?v=876228633754\r\n \r\nOn TheTapMusic, youâ€™ll be able to create an artist profile, upload your music and videos, blog, have your music play in our online radio player, be featured by TTM administrators, and sell your music directly through the site to music fans that discover you.  Everything is non-exclusive and totally free of charge.  Additionally, TheTapMusic team will be sending out monthly music samplers of the best music from TheTapMusic.com to our friends at record labels, ad agencies, and corporations to create more awareness about your work and hopefully get your music licensed!\r\n  \r\nAgain, it is totally free to sign-up for TheTapMusic, free to upload your tracks, free to get licensing deals, free to blog with us, and free to let fans know what youâ€™re all about.  Sounds too good to be true, right?  At The Tap we arenâ€™t just audiophiles, we are musicians, too.  We understand how tough the DIY method can be, so check out all we have to offer and make sure to tell your friends too. \r\n  \r\nWeâ€™d love to get your thoughts and feedback to help improve TheTapMusic.  This is a community for you, so once you sign up, make sure youâ€™re contacting us with any issues, feedback, requests, or concerns.  Your opinion is what matters most to our team.\r\n  \r\nWeâ€™ll send you a short survey a few days after youâ€™ve created your TTM account, and when you send it back youâ€™ll be entered to win a pretty cool prize!\r\n  \r\nOkay, well feel free to send me any questions, and I look forward to linking up with you on TheTapMusic.com\r\n\r\nCheers!',0,'1','Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; U; PPC Mac OS X 10.5; en-US; rv:1.9.2.12) Gecko/20101026 Firefox/3.6.12','',0,0),
