	(820,1,'2011-02-04 06:35:52','2011-02-04 06:35:52','http://vimeo.com/19553725\r\n\r\nKatya Rezvaya made a great film to \"Notes and Measures\" while she was in NYC - we have made it the official video','Notes and Measures','','publish','open','closed','','notes-and-measures-2','','','2011-06-22 14:50:19','2011-06-22 14:50:19','',0,'http://goodbyepicasso.com/?post_type=video&#038;p=820',0,'video','',0),
	(821,0,'2011-02-13 23:59:51','2011-02-13 23:59:51','We drove down from Milford PA (about 2 hours) to hear Spirit Family Reunion (who we\'d heard up here at a Music Festival 2 years ago, and who were performing right after your set).  We got there early and were INCREDIBLY happy we did.  What a great sound -- we\'re glad we bought the CD last night too.  You guys are going to go VERY far -- it will be nice to see you break through to the big time someday (I\'m thinking sooner than later).  If you ever would consider doing a private party (maybe) up here in Milford PA, shoot me an email.  If not, I think you\'re definitely worth seeing again and again -- even if NYC is two hours away (it\'s still where I grew-up).\r\n\r\nPowerful performance, poetic excellence, and the crazy eyes are a perfect performance.  WOW!\r\n\r\nSteve Shay\r\n570-296-3730\n<!--more-->\nAUTHOR: Steve Shay\nAUTHOR EMAIL: steveinmilford@yahoo.com\nAUTHOR URL: \nSUBJECT: [Goodbye Picasso] Contact\nIP: 24.102.170.178\nArray\n(\n    [Name] =&gt; Steve Shay\n    [Email] =&gt; steveinmilford@yahoo.com\n    [Website] =&gt; \n    [Message] =&gt; We drove down from Milford PA (about 2 hours) to hear Spirit Family Reunion (who we\'d heard up here at a Music Festival 2 years ago, and who were performing right after your set).  We got there early and were INCREDIBLY happy we did.  What a great sound -- we\'re glad we bought the CD last night too.  You guys are going to go VERY far -- it will be nice to see you break through to the big time someday (I\'m thinking sooner than later).  If you ever would consider doing a private party (maybe) up here in Milford PA, shoot me an email.  If not, I think you\'re definitely worth seeing again and again -- even if NYC is two hours away (it\'s still where I grew-up).\r\n\r\nPowerful performance, poetic excellence, and the crazy eyes are a perfect performance.  WOW!\r\n\r\nSteve Shay\r\n570-296-3730\n)\n','Steve Shay - 2011-02-13 23:59:51','','publish','open','open','','f4f27a4f88e6e48810c89d8ceb260fe9','','','2011-02-13 23:59:51','2011-02-13 23:59:51','',7,'http://goodbyepicasso.com/?post_type=feedback&p=821',0,'feedback','',0),
	(822,1,'2011-04-30 19:57:46','2011-04-30 19:57:46','On 7/25/02, Chris Dreyer and I played a gig at JP\'s in Valdosta, Georgia. Before the show, we sat in Chris\'s Jeep in the parking lot, drank the better part of a 12 pack, and listened to just-released Don\'t Know Why by Norah Jones about 30 times. We played 3 songs that night before the gig was stopped because of dismal attendance. Last night, we shared the bill with a Norah Jones side project and met her in the green room.','Norah','','publish','open','open','','norah','','','2011-04-30 19:58:36','2011-04-30 19:58:36','',0,'http://goodbyepicasso.com/?p=822',0,'post','',0),
