	(844,0,'2011-09-27 16:34:24','2011-09-27 16:34:24','Dear Goodbye Picasso,\r\n\r\nI represent independent and signed artists for MuseIQ a boutique music agency based in the emerging, creative Bushwick area of Brooklyn, New York. I was wondering if you would be interested in licensing your music for TV/film/web opportunities we receive?\r\n\r\nWe\'re comprised of pop industry vets who have worked with many top names in the music industry including Bjork, Morrissey, Neneh Cherry, Sneaker Pimps, Led Zeppelin, Tom Jones, Elvis Costello, and Underworld. We have already established ourselves by garnering an impressive amount of placements in the U.S. and Europe. We currently have a Paris-based partnership with the largest licensing agency in Europe that has given our U.S based artists placements in the global community.\r\n\r\nRecent placements include Amazon.com, Marriott Hotels, Havaianas Sandals, Kia Motors, EstÃ©e Lauder, Timberland, Max Mara, Piaget, Clinton Foundation, Asheville, Quincy Productions, Gocharge phone and 350.org.\r\n\r\nWe offer a non-exclusive agreement, 50/50 split on all license fees generated, you retain all rights to your material. \r\n\r\nIf this is of interest please feel free to contact me with any questions, I\'d be more than happy to discuss this in more detail or send you the agreement to look over.  If you\'re in the \'hood feel free to swing by the studio for a chat and a cup of tea!\r\n\r\nSincerely,\r\n\r\nSpencer Cobrin\r\n--\r\nMuseIQ â€œAn enlightened way to license original music for TV, film and the web\"\r\nCell: +1.917.804.9315 | Office: +1.718.381.3162\r\n119 Ingraham Street, Suite 423\r\nBrooklyn, New York, 11237, USA\r\nhttp://www.recordshop.museiq.tv/\n<!--more-->\nAUTHOR: Spencer Cobrin\nAUTHOR EMAIL: spencer@museiq.tv\nAUTHOR URL: http://www.recordshop.museiq.tv/\nSUBJECT: [Goodbye Picasso] Contact\nIP: 216.156.96.42\nArray\n(\n    [Name] =&gt; Spencer Cobrin\n    [Email] =&gt; spencer@museiq.tv\n    [Website] =&gt; http://w